  "title": "kids gym and dance teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Kids Gymnastics / Movement Teacher (Part-Time | Weekends)</strong></p><h2><strong>Location</strong></h2><p><strong>City Hall – Raffles City, Singapore</strong></p><h2><strong>Start Date</strong></h2><p><strong>February 2026</strong></p><h2><strong>About the Role</strong></h2><p>We are seeking a <strong>qualified and passionate Kids Gymnastics / Movement Teacher</strong> to conduct weekend evening classes for young children aged <strong>3 to 9 years old</strong>.</p><p>The role focuses on <strong>movement, stretching, balance, coordination, and mindful focus</strong>, delivered in a fun, safe, and engaging environment.</p><h2><strong>Class Types</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Kids Stretching Class</p></li><li><p>Kids Balance & Coordination Class</p></li><li><p>Kids Kind Focus & Mindful Movement Class<br />kids dance </p></li></ul><h2><strong>Working Schedule</strong></h2><ul><li><p><strong>Saturday & Sunday</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>5:00 PM – 8:00 PM</strong></p></li><li><p>Weekend evening commitment required</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Plan and conduct age-appropriate movement and gymnastics-based classes for children aged 3–9</p></li><li><p>Create a safe, structured, and fun learning environment</p></li><li><p>Engage, manage, and motivate children with different energy levels and abilities</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper warm-up, stretching, balance, and coordination activities</p></li><li><p>Maintain class discipline while keeping sessions enjoyable and interactive</p></li><li><p>Communicate clearly with studio management regarding class progress and needs</p></li><li><p>Ensure safety, hygiene, and child well-being at all times</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Relevant qualification in <strong>Gymnastics, Physical Education, Movement Training, Dance, or Child Development</strong></p></li><li><p>Proven experience teaching and managing young children (ages 3–9)</p></li><li><p>Strong classroom management and child engagement skills</p></li><li><p>Energetic, patient, and nurturing personality</p></li><li><p>Ability to entertain, motivate, and build trust with children</p></li><li><p>Weekend availability and reliability</p></li><li><p>First Aid / Child Safety certification is an advantage</p></li></ul><h2><strong>What We Offer</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Supportive and professional studio environment</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to grow with a new kids movement program</p></li><li><p>Competitive remuneration</p></li><li><p>Salary and further details <strong>to be discussed</strong> based on experience and suitability</p></li></ul>",
